<!DOCTYPE gui SYSTEM "kpartgui.dtd">
<gui name="musiclib" version="3">
  <!-- Menu layout is handled by KXmlGuiWindow defaults.
       Custom actions (e.g. MusicLib Handbook, Configure Toolbars) are
       injected programmatically after setupGUI().

       Toolbar management is fully programmatic via MainWindow::setupToolbar()
       and MainWindow::rebuildToolbar().  Configurable toolbar actions and
       their stable IDs (ToolbarItemId enum) are:

         Album        = 2   — Show album details for current track
         Playlist     = 3   — Playlist label + dropdown selector
         Audacious    = 4   — Launch / raise Audacious
         Kid3         = 5   — Open current track in Kid3 tag editor
         Dolphin      = 6   — Open track folder in Dolphin
         RipCD        = 7   — Launch / raise K3b CD ripper
                              (disabled when K3B_INSTALLED=false)

       The Rip CD action (RipCD) was added in Tasking 4 of the K3b
       integration plan.  It is wired to MainWindow::onRipCdTriggered()
       and implements four scenarios (A-D) covering all K3b running/stopped
       states and musiclib-vs-independently-launched detection via a PID file
       at ~/.config/musiclib/k3b.pid.
  -->
</gui>
